# Git LFS — only for genuinely large media that doesn't belong in git's
# regular object storage. Images stay OUT of LFS because Vercel does not
# pull LFS objects during build (it would deploy 131-byte pointer files
# in place of the real PNGs/JPEGs, breaking OG previews and on-page assets).
#
# Add a pattern back to LFS only if the assets are >5MB and rarely change.
# OG images, favicons, headshots, screenshots — keep as regular git blobs.
*.mp4 filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.mov filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
